    {
      "id": "f9b86e16-680e-4266-8841-900137da9638",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $A=\\left(\\begin{smallmatrix}1&1&1&1\\cr -1&1&-1&1\\cr -1&1&1&-1\\cr -1&-1&1&1\\cr\\end{smallmatrix}\\right)$.\\par",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A=\\left(\\begin{smallmatrix}1&amp;1&amp;1&amp;1\\cr -1&amp;1&amp;-1&amp;1\\cr -1&amp;1&amp;1&amp;-1\\cr -1&amp;-1&amp;1&amp;1\\cr\\end{smallmatrix}\\right)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "789279d2-bf52-47af-a0fd-bea2e1071064",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer $\\det A$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\det A\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2549af73-e207-4c5c-9251-f604a26e2c13",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer $(A-xI)(\\,{}^t\\!A-xI)$ et en déduire $\\chi_A(x)$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\((A-xI)(\\,{}^t\\!A-xI)\\)</span> et en déduire <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\chi_A(x)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "6eeb7434-bc13-4311-b759-be3f92209ee7",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $A$ est $\\C$-diagonalisable.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> est <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\C\\)</span>-diagonalisable.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "fe9d5632-b41b-4ef3-9075-c909a3cb9182",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$(A-xI)(\\,{}^t\\!A-xI) = (x^2-2x+4)I$, $\\chi_A(x) = x^2-2x+4$.\n$\\,{}^t\\!A = 2I-A$ donc $(A-xI)((2-x)I-A) = (x^2-2x+4)I$.\n             En prenant pour $x$ une des racines du polynôme $x^2-2x+4$, on obtient\n             un polynôme scindé à racines simples annulant $A$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\((A-xI)(\\,{}^t\\!A-xI) = (x^2-2x+4)I\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\chi_A(x) = x^2-2x+4\\)</span>. <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\,{}^t\\!A = 2I-A\\)</span> donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\((A-xI)((2-x)I-A) = (x^2-2x+4)I\\)</span>. En prenant pour <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x\\)</span> une des racines du polynôme <span class=\"math inline\">\\(x^2-2x+4\\)</span>, on obtient un polynôme scindé à racines simples annulant <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ]
